 cari yıl üretimimi karşılaştır.\\\" üretim tarafıyla ilgilenen kullanıcılar ve üst yönetim tarafından sık sorulur.\",\"En fazla üretim yapan 10 acenteyi / Akdeniz bölgesinde en fazla üretim yapan 10 acente / xxx no'lu acentenin en yüksek prime sahip ilk 10 müşterisini getir sık sorulan sorular arasındadır.\",\"No direct PII markers inferred from Excel metadata.\",\"Contains customer-identifying fields; apply least-privilege and masking in broad extracts.\",\"PII columns restricted: MUSTERI_ADI, MUSTERI_NUMARASI, MUSTERI_SOYADI\",\"Apply selective date filters for production reporting queries.\",\"Prefer key-based joins observed in workbook join definitions.\"],\"mandatory_rules\":[],\"retrieval_debug\":{\"selected_count\":20,\"total_documents\":20,\"effective_top_k\":200,\"min_score_threshold\":0.005,\"metadata_source\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\ky4642\\\\talk-to-your-data-v0\\\\metadata\\\\agents\\\\metadata_vectored_uretim.json\"}}\n\nSQL_CANDIDATES:\noption_1:\nSQL: SELECT SUM(fpe.BRUT_PRIM_TL) AS PRIM_TL  \nFROM AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_EK fpe  \nJOIN AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET ppo ON fpe.POLICE_ID = ppo.POLICE_ID  \nJOIN AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH gt ON ppo.TANZIM_TARIH_ID = gt.TARIH_ID  \nWHERE gt.TARIH = :report_period  \nFETCH FIRST 200 ROWS ONLY\nEXPLANATION: Question answered: What is the total gross premium (BRUT_PRIM_TL) for policies with a specific effective date (report_period)?  \nTables used: AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_EK, AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET, AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH  \nFilters: Only policies with an effective date matching the specified report_period are included.  \nGrouping/measures: The query sums the BRUT_PRIM_TL column to calculate the total gross premium.  \nExpected output columns: PRIM_TL (total gross premium)  \nAssumptions: The report_period is a specific date provided as a parameter. The query assumes that the effective date is stored in the GNL_TARIH table and linked via TANZIM_TARIH_ID.\n\noption_2:\nSQL: SELECT SUM(fpta.VOP_TL) AS PRIM_TL  \nFROM AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_TEM_ASSET fpta  \nJOIN AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET ppo ON fpta.POLICE_ID = ppo.POLICE_ID  \nJOIN AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH gt ON ppo.TANZIM_TARIH_ID = gt.TARIH_ID  \nWHERE gt.TARIH = :report_period  \nFETCH FIRST 200 ROWS ONLY\nEXPLANATION: Question answered: What is the total primary value (VOP_TL) of policies for a specific reporting period?  \nTables used: AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_TEM_ASSET, AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET, AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH  \nFilters: Only records where the date in GNL_TARIH matches the specified report period (:report_period)  \nGrouping/measures: Summing the VOP_TL column from the FACT_POL_POLICE_TEM_ASSET table  \nExpected output columns: PRIM_TL (total primary value)  \nAssumptions: The query assumes that the report_period input corresponds to a valid date in the GNL_TARIH table, and that VOP_TL represents a meaningful business metric like premium or value.\n\noption_3:\nSQL: SELECT SUM(ppo.POLICE_SAYISI) * AVG(fpe.BRUT_PRIM_TL) AS PRIM_TL  \nFROM AS_DWH.POLICE_SAYISI ps  \nJOIN AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET ppo ON ps.POLICE_ID = ppo.POLICE_ID  \nJOIN AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_EK fpe ON ppo.POLICE_ID = fpe.POLICE_ID  \nJOIN AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH gt ON ppo.TANZIM_TARIH_ID = gt.TARIH_ID  \nWHERE gt.TARIH = :report_period  \nGROUP BY ppo.POLICE_ID  \nFETCH FIRST 200 ROWS ONLY\nEXPLANATION: Question answered: What is the total premium amount (in Turkish Lira) for policies issued in a specific reporting period, calculated as the sum of policy counts multiplied by the average premium per policy? The result is limited to the first 200 rows.\n\nTables used: \n- AS_DWH.POLICE_SAYISI (ps)\n- AS_DWH.POL_POLICE_OZET (ppo)\n- AS_DWH.FACT_POL_POLICE_EK (fpe)\n- AS_DWH.GNL_TARIH (gt)\n\nFilters: \n- Policies with a policy date matching the specified reporting period (`gt.TARIH = :report_period`).\n\nGrouping/measures: \n- Grouped by `ppo.POLICE_ID`.\n- Measures include the sum of policy counts (`SUM(ppo.POLICE_SAYISI)`) multiplied by the average premium (`AVG(fpe.BRUT_PRIM_TL)`).\n\nExpected output columns: \n- PRIM_TL: Total premium amount calculated per policy.\n\nAssumptions: \n- The query assumes that the `:report_period` parameter is provided to filter policies by their effective date.\n- The multiplication of policy count and average premium per policy is a valid business calculation for total premium.\n- The `FETCH FIRST 200 ROWS ONLY` clause limits output size, likely for performance or display purposes."}
